<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-30"><hi rend="italic">September 30,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Barber relieved by Secretary of the Navy on account of ill health and
                            Newell substituted, who will report at once, so that commission can
                            start immediately.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>